<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-803-602  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 803 602.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  August 27 1990 v12 n35 p38(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>4GLs enhance application designers' productivity.andO;(fourth-generation languages)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mace, Scott.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Fourth-generation programming languages (4GLs) are intended toincrease the productivity of applications programmers by using alanguage designed specifically for database technology.andP;  Theproliferation of microcomputers at the expense of dumb terminalsin the Unix database management system market is causing 4GLvendors such as Informix, Ingres, Progress and Unify to upgradetheir technologies to accommodate the changes.andP;  Among the featuresbeing added to the languages are referential integrity and otherback-end features, graphical user interfaces and other front-endfeatures, and object-oriented programming and other paradigms.andO;Different vendors define a 4GL very differently, and users must besure they understand what they are getting from a vendor.andP;  Manycomputer-aided software engineering (CASE) tools generate 4GL codeas their product, but the most important aspect of the languagesis the increased productivity they provide over 3GL interfaces.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Fourth-Generation LanguagesProgram Development TechniquesNew TechniqueTechnologyApplications ProgrammingData Base Management SystemsUNIXProductivityEnhancements.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>